  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "CAPTAIN/ SUPERVISOR WAITER/ WAITRESS",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><p>1. Supervise and guide junior service crews/ waiter/ waitress.</p><p>2. Prepare tables for meals, including setting up items such as linens, silverware and glassware. Arrange tables and dining areas.</p><p>3. Fill salt, pepper, sugar, cream, condiment and napkin containers. Stock serving station or dining areas with supplies.</p><p>4. Stock service areas with supplies such as coffee, food, tableware and linens.</p><p>5. Prepare hot and cold beverages in the machine.</p><p>6. Greet guest and welcome them.</p><p>7. Escort customers to their tables and assist guests with seating arrangement.</p><p>8. Assist cashier by answering phones to take reservations and by greeting, seating and thanking guest.</p><p>9. Remove dishes and glasses from tables or counters and take them to kitchen for cleaning.</p><p>10. Clean tables or counters after patrons have finished dining.</p><p>11.  Perform cleaning duties such as sweeping, mopping floors, and taking out trash.</p><p>12.  Adhere to all relevant food hygiene & safety house rules.</p><p><u><strong>Cashiering Job Scope (When needed)</strong></u></p><p>1. Receive payments and present change to customers</p><p>2. Function as the host/hostess of the restaurant</p><p>3. Make reservations for customers</p><p>4. Appeal to impatient or irritated customers, especially during rush hours</p><p>5. Manage the register, including all credit card and cash operations</p><p>6. Ensure a balance of the register at the end of the shift or working period</p><p>7. Answer the restaurant telephone for enquiries and reservations</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>",
